  <source>Cornell University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the efficacy of iron (12.5 mg as ferrous sulfate) and
      placebo given for 6 months in preventing the elevation of blood lead concentration in
      children 6-9 months of age.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
